  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Motion Graphic Designer",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a <strong>senior, game-industry–experienced Motion Graphics Designer</strong> to join our Singapore team. In this role, you will take a leading position in bringing game worlds to life through high-impact visual content — from gameplay trailers to major marketing assets — combining strong storytelling, refined visual rhythm, and technical excellence.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the creation of high-quality <strong>gameplay trailers</strong> using in-game footage, with strong control over pacing, emotion, and narrative flow</li><li>Produce <strong>version update and promotional videos</strong> that resonate with players and align with game release cycles</li><li>Support and contribute to <strong>basic live-action shoots</strong>, including filming setup, lighting, color grading, and creative direction</li><li>Design polished <strong>motion graphics and kinetic typography</strong> with strong fundamentals in composition, animation, and visual hierarchy</li><li>Continuously refine production workflows and explore <strong>AI-assisted tools</strong> to enhance creative efficiency and output quality</li><li>Collaborate closely with <strong>game art, publishing, marketing, and live operations teams</strong> to ensure visual content aligns with brand identity and product goals</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Minimum 4 years of experience</strong> in motion design, video editing, or multimedia production</li><li><strong>Prior experience in a game studio or game-focused creative team is strongly preferred</strong></li><li>Strong sense of timing, music, and visual storytelling; able to independently deliver senior-level work</li><li>Proficiency in <strong>Adobe After Effects, Premiere Pro</strong>, and related motion design tools</li><li>Solid understanding of filming techniques, lighting, and color correction</li><li>Strong foundation in typography, animation principles, and visual composition</li><li>Passionate about gaming, familiar with player communities, content trends, and game marketing rhythms</li><li>Curious, open-minded, and motivated to explore new creative technologies, including AI-enabled tools</li></ul><p><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Monthly salary: SGD 7,000 – 8,000</strong>, commensurate with experience</li><li><strong>Minimum 15 months’ annual salary</strong></li><li>Senior candidates with strong game titles and portfolios may be considered at a higher level</li></ul>",
